<article class="comment" id="comment5766444" data-author="users/127956" data-subject="comments/5766444" data-dislikes="1" data-id="5766444">
<p class="avatar"><a rel="nofollow" title="carlos82" href="/users/carlos82"><img class="framed lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCA4MCA4MCI+PC9zdmc+" width="80" height="80" data-original="https://images.pushsquare.com/users/127956/avatar.jpg?v=1615718544" alt="carlos82" /></a></p>
<div class="detail"><ul class="info"><li class=" first"><a class="num" rel="nofollow" href="news/2020/08/ghost_of_tsushima_has_the_most_impressive_metacritic_user_score_of_the_console_generation#comment5766444">13</a></li><li><a rel="nofollow" class="username accent" title="carlos82" href="/users/carlos82">carlos82</a></li><li class=" last"><time class="date age " datetime="2020-08-13T15:08:53+00:00"><span>Thu 13th Aug 2020</span></time></li></ul>
<section class="text">
<p>I think some of it is because of the frankly silly reactions to TLOU2, I regularly see it on here or Facebook, where every mention of GOT is seemingly accompanied by comments of its better than TLOU2. Don't get me wrong this is a fine game but I don't see it as being anywhere near the best of this generation, its very pretty, the combat is very entertaining and main story is great if a little short. That said its open world is very much by the numbers with a lot of bloat, AI for stealth is hopeless at times, the camera is atrocious and its far too easy once you're fully upgraded (which is also very easy to do).</p>
<p>Something around a 7 or 8 for me, certainly not up there with the likes of God of War, Spider-Man, Horizon or TLOU2 but probably just above Days Gone in terms of exclusives</p>
</section>
