<article class="comment" id="comment5766851" data-author="users/267568" data-subject="comments/5766851" data-dislikes="0" data-id="5766851">
<p class="avatar"><a rel="nofollow" title="deSade57" href="/users/deSade57"><img class="framed lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCA4MCA4MCI+PC9zdmc+" width="80" height="80" data-original="https://images.pushsquare.com/users/267568/avatar.jpg?v=1595243336" alt="deSade57" /></a></p>
<div class="detail"><ul class="info"><li class=" first"><a class="num" rel="nofollow" href="news/2020/08/ghost_of_tsushima_has_the_most_impressive_metacritic_user_score_of_the_console_generation#comment5766851">36</a></li><li><a rel="nofollow" class="username accent" title="deSade57" href="/users/deSade57">deSade57</a></li><li class=" last"><time class="date age " datetime="2020-08-13T18:09:36+00:00"><span>Thu 13th Aug 2020</span></time></li></ul>
<section class="text">
<p>I don't get it. I thought Ghost of Tsushima was a good game, but had a fair few visual glitches, the story was quite a basic tale of revenge and didn't really flow that well in my opinion (the frequent interruptions to start a new tale was overdone), and the only character I thought was well written was Khotun Khan.</p>
<p>That sounds really negative, but I did enjoy the game too - I just don't think it is the classic people are making out.</p>
</section>
