<p><a href="https://www.pushsquare.com/users/BalsBigBrother" class="mention" data-username="BalsBigBrother" rel="nofollow">@BalsBigBrother</a> I think I read somewhere that disagreement between people actually causes mental distress that's akin to pain. People are also really ego-centric. Everyone. 100 percent of the time. Everyone also wants to be right. <br />Add the fact that a lot of people aren't capable of introspective thought, and you get people that feel as if you you just murdered their mother for saying something they disagree with, and a discourse you intended you have turns into discord that doesn't stop, a positive feedback loop of nothing anyone says matters.</p></section>
